  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a rectangular circuit diagram with a battery, two closed switches, and three resistors. The circuit has three vertical branches and two horizontal branches. The left vertical branch has the battery. From top to bottom, the middle vertical branch has a resistor labeled R sub 1, and a closed switch. The right vertical branch has a resistor labeled R sub 2. The bottom horizontal branch has a resistor labeled R sub 3 between the middle and right vertical branches. The top horizontal branch has a closed switch between the middle and right vertical branches.\" src=\"/images/3446f6504adb2356d83b32784fd69ce6.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A circuit consists of a battery, two switches, and three resistors <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R sub 1\"><math alttext=\"R sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mtext>R</mtext><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R sub 2\"><math alttext=\"R sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span>, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R sub 3\"><math alttext=\"R sub 3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math></span></span>, connected as shown in the figure. Which resistor(s) have a current when both switches are closed, and what reasoning supports the claim?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i4",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Only <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R sub 1\"><math alttext=\"R sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> has a current. <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R sub 1\"><math alttext=\"R sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> is the closest resistor to the battery.</p>",
